http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com: "A mediator can mediate an action over a bus of actors.  It does the following: 1. Accepts an action in {@link Mediator#mediate}. 2. Sends the action to the bus to test its applicability on all actors. 3. It _mediates_ over these test results. 4. It selects the _best_ actor. 5. The action is run by the _best_ actor, and the result if returned.  The _mediates_ and _best_ parts are filled in by subclasses of this abstract Mediator class."
